## 4. Round System

Added support for multiple rounds running in parallel.

Enhance the existing Million Pot Game frontend to support multiple rounds.

Do not rebuild the app. Only extend the current logic and UI.

GAME LOGIC:

- When a round fails (pot exceeds $1,000,000):
  - Mark the current round as FAILED
  - Allow players to claim refunds from this round
  - Immediately start a new round

- Each round must have its own state:
  - roundId
  - pot value
  - status (Active, Won, Failed)
  - user deposits

- Refunds belong only to the round where the user deposited

NEW UI REQUIREMENT:

Add a “Round System” to the interface.

Top section:
- Show current active round:
  - “Round #2”
  - Pot value
  - Target: $1,000,000

Below that, add a section called:

“Previous Rounds”

Each previous round card should show:
- Round number
- Status (Won / Failed)
- Button: “Claim Refund” (only if Failed)
- Button: “View Details”

USER FLOW:

- Users can deposit only in the active round
- If a round fails:
  - The UI switches automatically to the new round
- Users can still scroll down and claim refunds from old rounds

IMPORTANT:

- Do not mix funds between rounds
- Each round must be independent
- Refund button should only affect that specific round
- Hide “Add Crypto” button for failed rounds

UI STYLE:

- Mobile-first
- Clean card layout
- Clear separation between current round and previous rounds

For now:
- Use mock data
- Simulate round transitions
- Do not connect to blockchain yet

GOAL:

Create a smooth user experience where:
- The game never stops
- New rounds start instantly
- Players can safely claim refunds from previous rounds

